<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-PLUMMER-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLUMMER CLOSE TO LONG-TERM DEAL  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE Schoenfeld  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - Second-year quarterback Jake Plummer will sign a
four-year contract extension with the Cardinals today, likely
making him the highest-paid player in team history.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals have scheduled an 11 a.m. news conference but
refuse to discuss the details.
</P>
<P>
   A source close to Plummer said his agent, Leigh Steinberg, and
the team were hammering out details Sunday night and expected to
complete them this morning.
</P>
<P>
   The deal is expected to be for substantially more than $5
million a year, the going rate for young starting quarterbacks.
</P>
<P>
   Another Steinberg client, Rob Johnson of Buffalo, signed a
five-year, $25 million contract last spring that included an $8
million signing bonus.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals, who still are $3 million under the 1998 salary
cap, could count some of Plummer's pro-rated signing bonus against
this year's cap.
</P>
<P>
   Steinberg told ``The Arizona Republic'' that he has talked often
with Cardinals officials recently about a new deal for Plummer, who
has one year remaining on his rookie contract that averages
$545,000 a year. He earned $362,500 this year, one of the lowest
totals for a starting quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   By signing Plummer to the extension, the team will have its most
important and popular player under contract through the 2002
season. It also means the team will not have to use the
``franchise'' designation on him.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not right there, but we're close,'' Steinberg said of
negotiations. ``It could happen. There still are a few things to
work out, but I think we can get it done.''
</P>
<P>
   Steinberg and his associate, David Dunn, attended Sunday's 19-17
victory over the New Orleans Saints, a game in which Plummer drove
the Cardinals 73 yards in the final 81 seconds for the winning
score.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
