<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Computer games don't have to cost anything
 &HT;    By Bill Husted
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If holiday shopping has cut into your budget for
computer games, you needn't fear withdrawal. Many games are
available free for the downloading on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   Some of these games fall into the shareware category: You
download them free and then are expected to pay if you like and
continue to use the game. Many of the shareware games are
full-blown versions, while others have only a few episodes.
</P>
<P>
   Other games available for free downloading are demonstration
versions of commercial games. In that case, the games are usually
crippled to one degree or another. Either you get only a few
episodes of an elaborate game, or some of the features of the game
have been disabled. Think of these commercial demos as, at worst, a
good way to preview a game before making the sometimes-expensive
purchase.
</P>
<P>
   Our first Web site has a mixture of both types _ shareware and
commercial demos. The site is called the Ultimate Game Download
site and you'll find it at http://www.skyex.com/rkonline/dwnld.htm.
Like many programs available for download on the Net, these games
come in a file that is compressed into something called a ZIP file.
That means you'll need software to decompress the ZIP file.
</P>
<P>
   Many computer users already have such a program, but if you
don't have one, just use the term ``ZIP'' as a search word and pick
from the list of unzipping programs at a site like those at
http://www.shareware.com and
</P>
<P>
   http://www.download.com.
</P>
<P>
   The ease of downloading from the Ultimate Game Download site
varies considerably from game to game. One reason for that is most
of the game downloads are not actually stored at the computer that
holds the Web site. Instead, the games are stored on sites
maintained by their publishers or owners. Some of these sites are
extremely busy and _ in extreme cases _ may refuse to make the
connection. In that case, you'll be forced to try again.
</P>
<P>
   To the good, the site has literally dozens of games, including
commercial demos of some of the most popular games.
</P>
<P>
   You'll surely want to bookmark the next site _ Game Downer.
Download games and sites at
http://starcreations.com/gamedowner/ga-dwn01.htm. You can search
for games alphabetically here, making it easier to find a specific
game. Again, most games are not stored on the site, so download
times and availability may vary.
</P>
<P>
   This is just a sampling of the game sites you can find online.
To find a list of literally hundreds of sites that offer downloads,
try using your favorite search engine with the search terms ``game
download'' and, if you try them all, you'll be so busy downloading
you won't have time to play.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
