NORTHERN IRELAND, REASON FOR HOPE Peace in Northern Ireland now has
a chance - it's one of the success stories, hopefully, of 1998. By
Kevin Cullen. From The Boston Globe Magazine. Full-length (4,000
words) + edited article available. (Kevin Cullen is The Boston
Globe's London bureau chief. He has been covering the conflict in
Northern Ireland for more than a decade and lived there during the
year of the historic negotiations that culminated in the Good
Friday Agreement.)
_______________________________________________________________ 4.
THE AWESOME ODYSSEY OF SIR ERNEST SHACKLETON One of the most
perilous expeditions in the history of exploration was undertaken
by Anglo-Irishman Sir Ernest Shackleton during the First World War.
He failed in his goal - to be the first to cross the continent of
Antarctica - but accomplished much more by orchestrating a
legendary escape from the Antarctic winter and the gales of the
South Atlantic. By Klaus Bachmann. From GEO magazine. 3,000 words.
(English translation available.)
_______________________________________________________________ 5.
