burned down in October, a fringe environmental group took credit -
or so the world learned from Craig Rosebraugh, spokesman for the
fur-free vegan anarcho-cause. By Robert Sullivan. From The New York
Times Magazine. Full-length (3,000 words) + edited article
available. 6. THE GIFT OF GAB People can talk. Animals and birds
can use signals to attract, threaten or alert each other, but they
can't ask questions or strike bargains. Those skills make Homo
sapiens a uniquely successful, powerful and dangerous mammal.
Grooves and holes in fossil skulls may reveal when our ancestors
began to speak. The big question, though, is what drove them to it?
By Matt Cartmill. From Discover magazine. 1,000 words + photos.
