<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 12:44 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0415 &Cx1f; tab-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-WIN-A-PRIZE-ADVISORY-     12-21 0293
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WIN-A-PRIZE-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   HISTORY COMES ALIVE in Harold Evans' best seller, ``The American
Century,'' which captures the great events, personalities and
movements of the past 100 years.
</P>
<P>
   Now this engaging work is available to newspapers _ in short
bites of 100 words each. Use one a day in 1999, or compile them to
form weekly or monthly specials _ WITH ART!!!
</P>
<P>
   To celebrate the release of these excerpts, The New York Times
Syndicate is running a history trivia quiz based on ``The American
Century.'' Every day this week we will offer one question on the
wire. The first editor to fax back the correct answer will win a
copy of ``The American Century.''
</P>
<P>
   Here is today's question:
</P>
