<HEADLINE>
LANGE, SHUE TERRIFIC IN `COUSIN BETTE' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Cousin Bette'' _ Jessica Lange and Elisabeth
Shue team up to humiliate men. Actually, an aging Lange engages
Shue to destroy the men who jilted her. The only problem is that no
man in his right mind would reject the gorgeous Lange. The two
actresses, script, and direction are terrific.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Secret of Nimh 2'' _ The success of animated films on
video has led to many sequels, none more deserving than ``The
Secret of Nimh.'' While the technical qualities might not measure
up to Disney, the story involving animal lab research is
provocative and dramatic.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Rat Pack'' _ Whenever casting agents are looking for
actors to portray famous people, the first thing they go for is the
look. It's nearly always a mistake. In this case, Ray Liotta looks
nothing like Sinatra but he does try to capture the inner man.
Aided by Don Cheadle's Sammy Davis, Jr. and Bobby Slayton's Joey
Bishop, this film portrays the Vegas playboys better than ``Oceans
11,'' which starred the actual characters.
</P>
<P>
   ``Blade'' _ Wesley Snipes stars with Kris Kristofferson in the
biteless vampire movie.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, Fox Lorber is releasing five terrific music
biographical documentaries by the legendary Robert Mugge. ``Sonny
Rollins: Saxophone Colossus,'' ``The Gospel According to Al
Green,'' ``Black Wax: Gil Scott-Heron,'' ``The Return of Ruben
Blades,'' and ``Sun-Ra.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 29: ``The Avengers,'' ``Why Do Fools
Fall in Love,'' ``Montana,'' ``Knock Off,'' ``Baseketball.'' Jan.
5: ``Out of Sight,'' ``The Rescuers,'' ``How Stella Got Her Groove
Back,'' ``Every Mother's Fear,'' ``Dr. Who: The Mind of Evil,''
``Disturbing Behavior,'' ``Project Grizzly,'' ``Scarred City.''
Jan. 12: ``Wilde,'' ``Love and Death on Long Island,'' ``The Truman
Show,'' ``Our Mutual Friend,'' ``pi,'' ``Dance with Me,'' ``Henry
Fool,'' ``Fireworks,'' ``Sing and Dance with Barney,'' ``Wubbulous
World of Dr. Seuss.'' Jan. 19: ``Smoke Signals,'' ``Invasion
Earth,'' ``Mafia!,'' ``Because of Him,'' ``The Amazing Mrs.
Holliday,'' ``Slums of Beverly Hills,'' ``Evidence of Blood,''
``Buffalo Island,'' ``Little City,'' ``Buffalo 66.'' Jan. 26:
``Kurt and Courtney,'' ``Whatever,'' ``Cube,'' ``Rush Hour.'' Feb.
2: ``There's Something About Mary,'' ``Mulan,'' ``The Alarmist,''
``Brute Force,'' ``Shooting Fish,'' ``Who Am I?,'' ``Naked City,''
``Heaven or Vegas,'' ``The Blue Gardenia.'' Feb. 9: ``Next Stop
Wonderland,'' ``Rounders,'' ``Office Killer,'' ``The Invasion
Begins.'' Feb. 16: ``Snake Eyes. Feb. 23: ``Carnival of Souls.''
</P>
</TEXT>
