<DOCNO> NYT19981221.0206 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-21 14:08 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0564 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CHAIRS-HNS &LR;      12-21 0299
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHAIRS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OCCASIONAL CHAIRS, PERFECT ITEM FOR HOLIDAY SEASON 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM  
 c.1998 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ Chairs have been around since the ancient
Egyptians.
</P>
<P>
   But according to books on traditional decorating, the ottoman
was an auxiliary seat in American furnishings dating only to the
early 1840s, prior to the Victorian period, and so was the
occasional chair.
</P>
<P>
   A simple parlor, dining room or bedroom chair was customarily
used for this as-needed type of seating. The occasional chair
remains a favorite standby, especially for holiday dinners, parties
and family gatherings.
</P>
<P>
   Also called a transitional chair, it has often featured turned
wood parts and a rush or caned seat, although occasional chairs
with upholstered seats were commonly found in living rooms. It is
often a one-of-a-kind chair, ornate, with carvings, swags,
medallions, painted designs, oval- or shield-shaped backs, with or
without arms.
</P>
<P>
   However, an occasional chair also can be one that came from a
parlor set of four or six. Side chairs commonly fit the bill
because they can fit easily anywhere in the home, put aside until
needed. According to ``The Field Guide to American Victorian
Furniture,'' by Thomas H. Ormsbee, an Astor, Vanderbilt or similar
mansion would be provided with a quantity of these gilded wooden
side chairs to be held in reserve for formal dinners or musical
soirees. Another popular shape for an occasional chair was the
corner chair, where the diagonally placed seat forms a right angle
corner.
</P>
<P>
   Occasional chairs can be easily found in many yard, tag and
garage sales, as well as auctions and antiques shops. An occasional
chair can be found from as little as $3 to $3,000 or more.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
