complaint against Andersen Consulting, in which it said that the
consulting firm failed to ensure that the retailer's computer
merchandising system was prepared for the Year 2000. By Barnaby J.
Feder.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ECON (Tokyo) _ The Japanese government proposes a national
budget that aims to lift the economy out of recession, but its vast
size underscores the pressing worry that a big spending spree now
will break the official coffers later. By Sheryl WuDunn.
</P>
