(TRUMPET-STROKE-MED)
</P>
<P>
   -- The simple act of watching the mirror image of a healthy limb
may nudge a stroke-damaged limb back into action, according to
California brain researchers. (STROKE-MIRROR-MED)
</P>
<P>
   -- Allowing patients to return to work less than two weeks after
a certain type of spinal-disc surgery is just as safe as the
standard months-long recovery, new research suggests.
(BACK-SURGERY-MED)
</P>
