<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   PROS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-REEVES _ Falcons coach Dan Reeves is expected to remain in
the hospital for several days while doctors adjust medication. He
is under strict orders from doctors to not talk with Falcons, and
team officials say he might not make it back for the first game of
the playoffs. Reeves apparently did too much too soon and could not
get rest at home because of visits, calls. (Winkeljohn) 18-20''
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONSFEVER _ Picked to be a middle-of-the-pack team at the
beginning of the year, the Falcons have surpassed all expectations
by winning the NFC West. Talking to the new champs in Suwanee today
and updating ticket sales. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NOTES _ Falcons notebook. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-NOTES _ NFL notes rail. (Pasquarelli, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COACHES _ ATLANTA _ Many teams around the South are
preparing for bowl games with new coaches or depleted coaching
staffs. Former Georgia assistant Chris Scelfo is the new coach at
Tulane, and he must prepare for the liberty Bowl without much of a
staff to work with. Many of the former assistants under former
coach Tommy Bowden have joined their boss at Clemson. Florida will
face Syracuse in the Orange Bowl without its offensive and
defensive coordinator. Tennessee will meet Florida State in the
Fiesta Bowl without its offensive coordinator. David Cutcliffe, who
left Tennessee to become the coach at Ole Miss, won't have much of
a staff as many of the former assistants followed Tommy Tuberville
to Auburn. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKC-HOOPS _ Several interesting matchups highlight one of the
best nights of college basketball during the early portion of the
season. Georgia Tech follows its meeting with Kentucky on Saturday
by hosting North Carolina while Georgia and Georgia State also have
home games. However, the marquee matchup will feature Kentucky and
Duke in a rematch of last year's thrilling regional final won by
Kentucky. (Willingham, Atlanta-Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKC-GATECH-UNC _ Georgia Tech-North Carolina basketball advance.
(Arey, Atlanta-Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UGA-ECAR _ Georgia-East Carolina basketball advance.
(Schlabach, Atlanta-Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
