CLINTON-AZPOLL (Phoenix) - In an ``Arizona Republic'' poll
conducted after Saturday's impeachment, most Arizonans said they
feel the Senate should not force President Clinton from office, but
think he should be punished for his behavior in the Monica Lewinksy
scandal. Clinton's approval rating rose to its highest point in
years. Slightly more than half said they don't think Clinton should
resign. By MICHAEL MURPHY. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
