baseball and basketball, watches ``The Simpsons'' on TV, roams the
neighborhood on his bicycle and hates December. Not long ago, his
teacher in second grade asked her class to write an essay about the
holiday season. In big tilted letters printed on blue-lined paper
his began, ``I hate December because I don't celebrate Christmas.''
By E.J. MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
