</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-ECON (Rio de Janeiro, Brazil) _ Just a month ago, markets
here rallied as the International Monetary Fund moved toward
announcing its $41.3 billion bailout for Brazil. This month stocks
are bouncing wildly once again, but mostly in the opposite
direction. As of Friday, they were down 21.5 percent. By Diana Jean
Schemo.
</P>
