<HEADLINE>
LOTS OF SPORTS GAMES FOR KIDS FOUND AT THESE SITES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOMMY CUMMINGS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Attention kids: That big holiday gift overwhelming the others in
the front room might very well be a fully loaded, Internet-ready
computer this year.
</P>
<P>
   Attention parents: If that's the case _ and chances are the
youngsters have scratched off enough wrapping paper to tell _ it's
time to get acquainted with all of the youth-related sports Web
sites.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, before you visit any of these sites, make sure you're
loaded with the Macromedia Shockwave (www.macromedia.com) plug-in.
You'll need this handy downloadable free software for the many
interactive games found at these user-friendly sites:
</P>
<P>
   NFL (www.nfl.com/playfootball): The NFL's official site has
several Shockwave games, including Soak the Coach, a game in which
users control the coach, who has a new suit and is avoiding a
Goop-ade shower from his players.
</P>
<P>
   Another cool game is the 2-Minute Drill, a good place for those
knuckleheads who think Cowboys coach Chan Gailey has an easy job as
offensive coordinator. Simply direct the team of your choice _
select Cowboys for the challenge _ 70 yards for the winning
touchdown with two minutes remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Young users can also check out information about NFL-sponsored
flag football; punt, pass and kick contests and summer skill camps
and the always-popular take-a-player-to-school program.
</P>
<P>
   Major League Baseball (www.majorleaguebaseball.com): The site's
Fun and Games section has three interactive games. The best is Big
League Vendor, a game in which users toss hot dogs, peanuts and
beer to ballpark fans for points. Users must hit 7 of 10 targets to
advance to each level. It's not easy and, at the beer level, users
lose points for throwing a beer to a minor.
</P>
<P>
   The site's other interactive games are Batting Practice and
Relief Pitcher. If the site's games grow tiresome, it also has
links to sites featuring recent video-game releases.
</P>
<P>
   nhl4kids (www.nhl4kids.com): NHL.com, the league's official
site, has developed an impressive site for young NHL fans. It has
instructional sections (Yo, Coach and Hockey Talk), merchandise and
yes, several games.
</P>
<P>
   The best game might be Dress the Players, where the object is to
fully clothe a player or goalie in the proper sequence. Any mistake
_ such as putting on a glove before pants _ means the game won't
work.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sports Illustrated'' for Kids (www.sikids.com): Besides sports
advice and other features found in the magazine, the SI for Kids
site specializes in Shockwave games in all sports.
</P>
<P>
   One of the more popular is the Deion vs. Deion game in which
Deion Sanders battles himself as receiver and defensive back. The
best thing about this game: No worries about him injuring his toe.
</P>
<P>
   Football Frenzy is an interesting game, too. Players must battle
killer cheerleaders, crazed cheeseheads and a runaway army tank to
reach the end zone.
</P>
<P>
   The advice section takes on tough questions, including this
current post: ``What if you're not the best player on your team and
it seems like you're getting in the way?''
</P>
<P>
   CHAT HIGHLIGHTS: Orlando Miracle player Nykesha Sales is
scheduled to chat live on WNBA.com, the WNBA's official site, at
3:30 p.m. Tuesday ... San Diego Chargers linebacker Junior Seau on
NFL.com's Quarterback Club (www.nfl.com/qbclub) at 7 p.m. Tuesday
... Tampa Bay quarterback Trent Dilfer, 8 p.m. Tuesday, Team NFL on
America Online (keyword: live).
</P>
<P>
   BEST SPORTS SITE: ESPN.com was selected top sports site,
according to Yahoo! Internet Life in its third annual Top o' the
Net survey. CBS SportsLine was No. 2 and CNN/SI.com was No. 3.
</P>
<P>
   (Tommy Cummings writes about the Internet for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. You can contact him at (817) 390-7397. E-mail:
dragon(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the Star-Telegram's online
services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
