<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Tuesday, Dec.
22, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Bob
Schenet at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Seattle) _ If Seahawk management means to
bring in an established, big-name head coach, good luck. The
competition is stiff for the two biggest, Mike Holmgren and George
Seifert.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-CLINTON (Undated) _ Bill Clinton is the best performer the
presidency has ever had, Ronald Reagan's Hollywood credentials
notwithstanding. As long as he remains defiant on TV, right down to
the flexing of those jaw muscles, the message to Americans is
clear: ``My enemies are out to get me, but you and I are bigger
than this petty partisan squabble.''
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
