NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, DECEMBER 22
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-GIRL-KIDNEY-TRANSPLANT-NYT (moved on Friday, Dec. 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Dec. 4,
about the ethical quandary posed by a father's offer to donate his
one remaining kidney to his daughter misstated the source of the
phrase that contains the words ``do no harm.'' The phrase is from
Hippocrates' work ``Epidemics,'' not from the Hippocratic oath.
</P>
<P>
   BC-VENEZUELA-AD-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Friday, Dec. 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Dec. 4,
about a marketing battle between the Coca-Cola Company and in
Venezuela misstated the country's area relative to Texas. Venezuela
is 32 percent larger than Texas, not half the size.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-ROBOT-CLUB-GAME-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Dec. 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Dec. 9,
about the Robot Club computer game identified its developers
incompletely. In addition to Learn Technologies, they included
R.Greenberg Associates.
</P>
