</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONEYBAG _  &LR; Question: I have owned some shares in a stock for
five years, with an original cost of about $1,000. The current
market value is about $9,000. What are the tax consequences if I
give the stock to my son? What are the tax consequences if I give
the stock to charity instead? Columnist Arthur M. Louis has the
answers.
</P>
