<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COLD-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Miami Valley's weather gift: a cold, White Christmas
 &HT;    By Brandon Peterson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Brisk winds, a downpour of rain and a steep drop
in the temperature marked the first day of winter Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The weather probably won't get any better today. The high will
be just 18 degrees, according to Jeffrey Sites, meteorologist for
the National Weather Service.
</P>
<P>
   While snow is forecast this week, meteorologists predict a
fast-moving system will dump about an inch on the Miami Valley _
probably on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Sites said Christmas Eve skies will be partly sunny with highs
in the 20s.
</P>
<P>
   And for the third year in a row, meteorologists predict no white
Christmas.
</P>
<P>
   Although a trace of snow graced the ground last Christmas, the
last time the Miami Valley had a white Christmas was the 1 inches
that fell in 1995, said meteorologist Mark Tobin.
</P>
<P>
   With icy rain and snow headed for the Miami Valley, motorists
are advised to allow plenty of time to reach their destinations.
</P>
<P>
   As a steady rain fell Monday evening, police were dispatched to
dozens of accidents. None resulted in serious injuries. Police
expected more serious crashes when freezing weather caused wet
roads to ice over.
</P>
<P>
   To prepare for the hazardous conditions, the Ohio Highway Patrol
plans to dispatch additional patrol crews, said Lt. John Born. He
also said motorists should prepare for the worst.
</P>
<P>
   ``People should be equipped with emergency equipment in their
cars like flares, blankets, flashlights, batteries, cell phones or
CBs, jumper cables, candles and matches,'' Born said.
</P>
<P>
   He also urged motorists to wear seat belts and drive cautiously.
</P>
<P>
   Brandon Peterson writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-21-98 2309EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
